{"contacts": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1002037", "name": "dataset submitter"}, {"accession": "MS:1000586", "name": "contact name", "value": "Mark Adamo"}, {"accession": "MS:1000589", "name": "contact email", "value": "mark.e.adamo@dartmouth.edu"}, {"accession": "MS:1000590", "name": "contact affiliation", "value": "Dartmouth College"}]}, {"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1002332", "name": "lab head"}, {"accession": "MS:1000586", "name": "contact name", "value": "Arminja Kettenbach"}, {"accession": "MS:1000589", "name": "contact email", "value": "arminja.n.kettenbach@dartmouth.edu"}, {"accession": "MS:1000590", "name": "contact affiliation", "value": "The Geisel School of Medicine at Dartmouth"}]}], "description": "The shugoshin proteins are universal protectors of centromeric cohesin during mitosis and meiosis. The binding of human hSgo1 to the PP2A-B56 phosphatase through a coiled coil (CC) region mediates cohesion protection during mitosis. Here we undertook a structure function analysis of the PP2A-B56-hSgo1 complex, revealing unanticipated aspects of complex formation and function. We establish that a highly conserved pocket on the B56 regulatory subunit is required for hSgo1 binding and cohesion protection during mitosis in human somatic cells. Consistent with this, we show that hSgo1 blocks the binding of PP2A-B56 substrates containing a canonical B56 binding motif. We find that PP2A-B56 bound to hSgo1 dephosphorylates Cdk1 sites on hSgo1 itself to modulate cohesin interactions.  Collectively our work provides important insight into cohesion protection during mitosis.", "fullDatasetLinks": [{"accession": "MS:1002488", "name": "MassIVE dataset URI", "value": "http://massive.ucsd.edu/ProteoSAFe/dataset.jsp?task=14a705074bf44a6f95968e6b663b7b9e"}, {"accession": "MS:1002852", "name": "Dataset FTP location", "value": "ftp://massive.ucsd.edu/MSV000087003/"}], "identifiers": [{"accession": "MS:1002487", "name": "MassIVE dataset identifier", "value": "MSV000087003"}, {